## Resources

| Resource | Description |
|---|---|
| [debian_file](resources/file.md) | Manages a file on the remote host. |
| [debian_directory](resources/directory.md) | Manages a directory on the remote host. |
| [debian_user](resources/user.md) | Manages a local user account. |
| [debian_group](resources/group.md) | Manages a local group. |
| [debian_group_member](resources/group_member.md) | Manages a single user-group membership. |
| [debian_apt_packages](resources/apt_packages.md) | Manages a set of installed APT packages. |

## Data Sources

Data source results are stored in Terraform state. For sensitive data, use the equivalent ephemeral resource instead.

| Data Source | Description |
|---|---|
| [debian_command](data-sources/command.md) | Runs a command and returns its output. |
| [debian_file](data-sources/file.md) | Reads a file's contents and metadata. |
| [debian_release](data-sources/release.md) | Reads Debian release information from `/etc/os-release`. |

## Ephemeral Resources

Ephemeral resources work like data sources but their results are **not** persisted in Terraform state, making them suitable for sensitive or short-lived values.

| Ephemeral Resource | Description |
|---|---|
| [debian_command](ephemeral-resources/command.md) | Runs a command (output not stored in state). |
| [debian_file](ephemeral-resources/file.md) | Reads a file (contents not stored in state). |

## Actions

Actions are imperative operations that run once when invoked, outside the declarative plan/apply lifecycle.

| Action | Description |
|---|---|
| [debian_command](actions/command.md) | Runs an arbitrary command. |
| [debian_apt_update](actions/apt_update.md) | Refreshes the APT package index. |
| [debian_apt_upgrade](actions/apt_upgrade.md) | Upgrades installed packages. |
| [debian_systemctl_reload](actions/systemctl_reload.md) | Reloads a systemd unit. |
| [debian_systemctl_restart](actions/systemctl_restart.md) | Restarts a systemd unit. |
| [debian_systemctl_daemon_reload](actions/systemctl_daemon_reload.md) | Reloads all systemd unit files. |

